localStorage.setItem("w2a3","General plan needs to be put here today Me and Jon Tues 11am What do they want? They want to return the Printer and Stacker. EST: £24k Where are we?. I called 2 weeks ago with £5/£6k to resolve the issue and take back the Cutter Result: It became very clear very fast they primarily wanted £24k or at the very least £11500. The price of the cutter and parts spent I left with them Granting 6 weeks to resolve the below. Why do the want a refund? The three main complaints in decreasing order are. 3rd: The Ultrasonic cutter module rarely makes a couple of weeks, without a major issue. Needs significant attention and or parts. 2nd: Those parts are not cheap and considering they are on contract or guarantee they are confused on why? They also did not understand what triggers a charge? From now on they want to know prior to fitting parts and want us to look into the prices we have already charged. 1st The power stacker part does not stack more than a handful of labels and he says it never as. They needs 100 at a time and it rarely does that. My Findings. 1/ Material. Coles; Recycled 2 sided material. White and Black. Will Fray if not looped or sonically cut. The material is not what we demonstrated or quoted. I propose we do not formally know if this material is suited to ultrasonic cutting? Is it a quality material or a low cost material? Is it suited for purpose? Why do we not stock it? Is there a pertinent reason? 2/ Travis keeps adjusting things. This is our engineers main suggestion, but in fairness it could be argued that he does it because they have to get jobs out the door and he only tries after it already broke. Granted he often makes it worse, he says it's not actually him breaking it. Philip is open minded to both and says now he can't touch it. 3/ They mentioned static. Again the material and or foil could be an issue. The Air conditioning and or nylon carpets? The very dry storage area. Lots of cardboard and no open windows. 4/ memory curl on the material. The cores are quite small and I noticed a lot of material curl. As it is two sided it can be run upside down. This meant it curled up rather than down but this helped whilst I was there. 600 labels no problem. 5/ The stacker literally could be a lemon. It seems to works at our place and not at there's. Ours works ok at our place and not well at there's. Probably??? The others we have that work use different material and or foil but again this one could be a lemon! 6/ After watching them for two hours I noticed they seemed to spend quite some time adjusting the Nice label template. I explained that this is irregular. Once a template is set it should last months? They adjust it several times a day. After the meeting Tony informed me they may not be using the correct drivers. Possibly Cab? Either way even though we did not sell the software it is theoretically possible its wholly or partially to blame. We need to train them on nice label as it is no doubt playing some roll in the problem. Tues 12 May, Mark and Jon to Call 11am to look into everything but in particular look at software, static and anything else that stands out. Plus Charley needs training possibly at Soabar");
